sentences: Roopam Garg (born October 17, 1995) is an Indian-American musician, guitarist and composer.
In 2015, Garg enrolled at Berklee College of Music in Boston, Massachusetts.
He released his debut single Self Spiral leading up to an EP titled "Naked Awareness", followed by three singles in 2017 "Origami", "Lux", and "Echo End".
He graduated from Berklee in 2018, with a Bachelor of Music degree.
Garg also received the 2018 Berklee Performance-Division Guitar Scholarship Award.
In 2018, shortly after graduating, Garg performed at the UK Tech- Fest 2018 and Dissonance Festival 2018.
He rebranded his identity from The Surrealist to DARK in 2020 amidst the COVID-19 pandemic to signify his new direction in darker, ambient music.
The year 2019 represented a change in direction for Garg.
Guitar World has described his work as "some of the most compelling orchestral guitar music around today".
Later that year, he endorsed Kiesel Guitars as well as Stone Age Guitar Products.
